               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000048ja-1">The first Reading Terrace is said to have been built further up the Xuanweng Mountain on Huanxi Peak 歡喜岭 at the place where <persName ref="https://tinyurl.com/3ba47nfd">Yang Yin 楊愔</persName> of the  <term subtype="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000054">Northern Qi</term> (550-577) read. According to Liu Dapeng, the Reading Terrace was originally built in the 27th year of the <term subtype="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000051">Ming Jiajing period (1548)</term>. Located between the <placeName ref="/place/000048ka">Ancestor Lü Ge-Pavilion</placeName> on its south and the Triple Terrace Ge-Pavilion on its north.</p>
               </desc>
